criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Children with ASD or high risk for autism;

          -  Han ethic;

          -  Parents were at least middle school educated, and agreed to do at least 20 hours per
             week of planned practice activities with the child in daily life.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Children with Syndromic ASD caused by known genetic defects or inherited metabolic
             diseases , such as Rett Syndrome, Fragile X Syndrome, Angelman Syndrome, Prader-Willi
             Syndrome, tuberous sclerosis;

          -  Visual, auditory and physical disabilities;

          -  Complication with other serious chronic diseases, such as liver and kidney failure,
             connective tissue diseases, tumors.
